    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How it works Modal -->
  <div
    id="how-it-works-modal"
    class="fixed inset-0 bg-primary/20 backdrop-blur-sm z-50 flex items-center justify-center p-4 transition-all duration-300 hidden"
  >
    <div
      class="bg-canvas rounded-2xl max-w-lg w-full p-6 border border-hairline shadow-modal flex flex-col gap-4 animate-scale-in max-h-[85vh] overflow-y-auto"
    >
      <div
        class="flex justify-between items-center pb-2 border-b border-hairline-soft"
      >
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary">
          Readability Score Checker Guide
        </h3>
        <button
          type="button"
          id="close-modal-btn"
          class="text-stone hover:text-primary transition-all text-lg cursor-pointer"
        >
          ✕
        </button>
      </div>

      <div class="text-xs text-slate leading-relaxed flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary">
          1. What is Readability Scoring?
        </h4>
        <p>
          Readability scoring measures how easy a passage of text is to read and comprehend. It calculates scores based on variables like word counts, sentence lengths, and syllable counts. This tool helps writers, marketers, and developers optimize content for their target audience's reading grade level.
        </p>

        <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary">2. Key Features of this Tool</h4>
        <p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-4 flex flex-col gap-1.5 mt-1">
            <li>
              <strong>Multiple Formulas</strong>: Computes Flesch Reading Ease, Flesch-Kincaid Grade Level, and Gunning Fog Index simultaneously.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Interactive Highlighting</strong>: Evaluates sentences in real-time. Highlights hard-to-read sentences (yellow/red), passive voice (green), adverbs (blue), and complex words (pink/rose) to suggest simplifications.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Revision Comparison</strong>: Compare an original version side-by-side with a revised version to track readability improvements.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Saved Drafts</strong>: Store drafts locally in your browser storage to retrieve them later.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </p>

        <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary">
          3. 100% Client-Side and Private
        </h4>
        <p>
          This tool executes entirely in your browser using standard client-side JavaScript. No text data is sent to external servers, making it completely secure for editing sensitive documents, private emails, and copy.
        </p>
      </div>
      <button
        type="button"
        id="modal-ok-btn"
        class="button-primary text-xs py-2 px-5 mt-2 self-end cursor-pointer"
      >
        Got it
      </button>
    </div>
